FBIS3-19445 "drweu052_q_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-052 Document Type:Daily Report 17 Mar 1994 TURKEY UN Envoy Calms Fear of Military in Balkans TA1703113194 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 0935 GMT 17 Mar 94 TA1703113194 Ankara ANATOLIA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] New York, Mar. 17 (A.A.) -- Turkish Ambassador to the United Nations Inal Batu said Wednesday [16 March] that Turkey has always worked with discipline and faith in any UN mission it took part in. Batu quelled fears that Turkish involvement in the Balkans, which was Ottoman domain for 500 years, would be a contribution toward peace and not conquest [as received]. A meeting is expected to be held in New York between U.N. Peace Forces Operations (UNPROFOR) Commander Kofi Hannan [name as received] and Batu. Batu is expected to reiterate Turkey's readiness to contribute with a mechanized battalion of 1,000 troops, which could be deployed within a week. Batu also said that Ankara favors a solution which would allow the deployment of Turkish forces in the already secured regions in Bosnia-Herzegovina.
